<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-3543] Commit Log Allocator deadlock after first start with empty commitlog directory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3543</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While testing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3541&quot; title=&quot;Support timeuuid column names&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3541&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3541&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; at some point stress completely timed out.  I proceeded to shut the cluster down and 2/3 JVMs hang infinitely.  After a while, one of them logged:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;WARN 19:07:50,133 Some hints were not written before shutdown.  This is not supposed to happen.  You should (a) run repair, and (b) file a bug report
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12533334">CASSANDRA-3543</key>
            <summary>Commit Log Allocator deadlock after first start with empty commitlog directory</summary>
